The paper deals with querying incomplete data using logic theories, which is a common problem in databases (cs.DB) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of Description Logic (DL) and ontology-mediated queries (OMQ) also suggests a connection to logic (cs.LO). The paper also discusses the translation of queries into Datalog, which is a popular language for data management and processing (cs.DS). Finally, the paper deals with the design and implementation of a query language, which is a topic in software engineering (cs.SE).
